[l] In den USA duerfen Internet-Provider jetzt die Daten ihrer Kunden verkaufen. Und zwar nicht nur die Stammdaten, nein.In a party-line vote, House Republicans freed Internet service providers such as Verizon, AT&T and Comcast of protections approved just last year that had sought to limit what companies could do with information such as customer browsing habits, app usage history, location data and Social Security numbers.
